1 prac titioner licensing and practice issues, and such other areas as
2 authorized by the Licensed Professional Counselors Act.
3 C. The Board shall not recommend rules for promulgation unless
4 all applicable requirements of the Administrative Procedures Act
5 have been followed including, but not limited to, notice, rule
6 impact statements, and rule-making hearings.
7 D. Members of the Board shall serve without compensation but
8 may be reimbursed for expenses incurred in the performance of their
9 duties, as provided in the State Travel Reimbursement Act. The
10 Board is authorized to utilize the conference rooms of and obtain
11 administrative assistance from the State Board of Medical Licensure
12 and Supervision as required.
13 E. The Board is authorized and empowered to:
14 1. Establish and maintain a system of licensure and
15 certification pursuant to the provisions of the Licensed
16 Professional Counselors Act;
17 2. Adopt and enforce standards governing the professional
18 conduct of persons licensed pursuant to the provisions of the
19 Licensed Professional Counselors Act;
20 3. Lease office space for the purpose of operating and
21 maintaining a state office, and pay rent thereon; provided, however,
22 such state office shall not be located in or directly adjacent to
23 the office of any person licensed pursuant to the provisions of the
24 Licensed Professional Counselors Act;
ENGR. S. B. NO. 397 Page 4

1 4. Purchase office furniture, equipment, and supplies;
2 5. Employ such office personnel as may be necessary, and fix
3 and pay their salaries or wages;
4 6. Contract with state agencies for the purposes of
5 investigating written complaints regarding the conduct of persons
6 licensed pursuant to the provisions of the Licensed Professional
7 Counselors Act and obtaining administrative assistance as deemed
8 necessary by the Executive Director; and
9 7. Make such other expenditures as may be necessary in the
10 performance of its duties.
11 F. The Board shall employ an Executive Director. The Executive
12 Director shall be authorized to:
13 1. Employ and maintain an office staff;
14 2. Enter into contracts on behalf of the Board; and
15 3. Perform other duties on behalf of the Board as needed or
16 directed.
17 G. All employees and positions shall be placed in unclassified
18 status, exempt from the provisions of the Oklahoma Personnel Act.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
20 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
21 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
22 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
23 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
